        "id": 5145
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-12T12:12:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I could not get this to work using http.Client (like it worked in go/github).\nRequests only seem to work to this API when the Authorization header is explicitly set with token.",
      "parentUuid": "77b9c2d5_91ff06ae",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 30,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 30,
        "endChar": 19
      },
      "revId": "6bafdfa8cedde423ea3fc0cda8c2260b5dd0accf",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fd2848f8_3b7cd282",
        "filename": "go/travisci/travisci.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 30,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-12T12:20:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The problem is that this strongly implies a long-lived token since (from what I can tell) this token never gets refreshed.  We should be avoiding long-lived tokens in favor of short-lived tokens obtained from the GCE metadata server.  It\u0027s possible that this failed because the service account was not authorized in the TravisCI server?",
      "parentUuid": "9f8f8d07_cf73fc36",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 30,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 30,
        "endChar": 19
      },
      "revId": "6bafdfa8cedde423ea3fc0cda8c2260b5dd0accf",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1c036ee2_a8751343",
        "filename": "go/travisci/travisci.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 30,
      "author": {
        "id": 5145
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-12T13:02:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Unfortunately github api requires a real user with an email so it will be a skia.org account not a service account. The skia.org account will not have any special access anywhere.\n\nLet\u0027s talk about authentication to both github and travisci here. While starting out I did the simplest method to get it working but maybe there are better ways.\n\nFor github I used a personal access token: https://developer.github.com/v3/auth/ which I intended to store in metadata.\nI guess other option is to hit their authorizations end point https://developer.github.com/v3/oauth_authorizations/ but will need to store client id and client secret for that, so I figured storing access token would be somewhat equivalent.\n\nFor travis ci https://docs.travis-ci.com/api/#authentication\nI got an access token from https://github.com/settings/applications for travis ci",
      "parentUuid": "fd2848f8_3b7cd282",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 30,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 30,
        "endChar": 19
      },
      "revId": "6bafdfa8cedde423ea3fc0cda8c2260b5dd0accf",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "bf20da28_cc7d3126",
        "filename": "go/travisci/travisci.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 30,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-12T13:44:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "From what I\u0027m reading here, a service account can be used in a \"GitHub App\", whatever that means: https://developer.github.com/apps/differences-between-apps/\n\nIf you\u0027ve done the research and determined that authenticating as a service account is truly not possible, then let\u0027s add a lot of comments explaining why we need to do it this way.  It would be good to know if there is a plan to support them in the future so that we can switch as soon as it\u0027s enabled.",
      "parentUuid": "1c036ee2_a8751343",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 30,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 30,
        "endChar": 19
      },
      "revId": "6bafdfa8cedde423ea3fc0cda8c2260b5dd0accf",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "dcf72484_48cc316d",
        "filename": "go/travisci/travisci.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 30,
      "author": {
        "id": 5145
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-17T13:59:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "GitHub apps are like chrome apps, i.e. apps you run on Github to improve workflows: https://github.com/marketplace e.g. Travis CI is a github app and it probably uses a service account when it is talking to github that is not exposed to us.\n\nYes, I believe using a service account is not possible for the roller. Added comments here and in the github CL.",
      "parentUuid": "bf20da28_cc7d3126",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 30,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 30,
        "endChar": 19
      },
      "revId": "6bafdfa8cedde423ea3fc0cda8c2260b5dd0accf",
